## Superclaude Infrastructure

All agent infrastructure lives at `~/.claude/` (global). Project-local `.claude/` dirs are internal to those projects and must NEVER be modified by superclaude agents.

| Directory | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `~/.claude/rules/` | Auto-loaded rules (numbered order) |
| `~/.claude/agents/` | Specialist agents (available via /agents) |
| `~/.claude/skills/` | Slash commands and agent-loaded skills |
| `~/.claude/plans/` | Cross-project orchestration plans and state |
| `~/.claude/comms/` | Meta <-> Orch(s) communication bus (namespaced per orch) |
| `~/.claude/agent-memory/` | Persistent per-agent memory |
| `~/.claude/docs/` | Usage guide and historical references |

## Agent Hierarchy

| Level | Agent | Invocation | Role |
|-------|-------|------------|------|
| Strategic | Meta | `claude --agent meta` | Cross-project supervision, brainstorms with the user, writes plans and directives, manages comms bus, triages orch health. The user launches/kills orchs manually. |
| Infrastructure | Scaf | `claude --agent scaf` | Superclaude infrastructure specialist. Edits agents, hooks, rules, skills, settings.json. Receives directives from Meta. |
| Tactical | Orch | `claude --agent orch` or `claude --agent orch-<name>` | Executes plans, spawns workers, edits code, manages git, reports progress. Named instances for parallel work. |
| Worker | `w-merger`, `w-debugger`, `w-refactorer`, `w-reviewer`, `w-planner` | Via Agent tool | Scoped specialist tasks |

### Multi-Orch & Workspace

Full protocol: `~/.claude/rules/12-agent-hierarchy.md`. Comms format: `~/.claude/comms/README.md`. Named orch template: `~/.claude/docs/usage-guide.md`.

**All agents run from `<YOUR_WORKSPACE_ROOT>` as CWD** (e.g. `~/projects/`) — never from inside project directories.

## Key Rules (auto-loaded)
- `00-universal.md` — Read before edit, minimal changes, git discipline, stop conditions
- `05-coding-standards.md` — Language-specific standards (path-scoped)
- `10-orchestrator-protocol.md` — Plan/state protocol (in-project and superclaude)
- `12-agent-hierarchy.md` — Meta/Orch/Worker hierarchy, write scopes, multi-orch comms
- `15-programming-principles.md` — 10 programming principles (DRY, KISS, etc.)
